sentence: Procter & Gamble Co ( PG ) files its latest 10-K with SEC for the fiscal year ended on June 30, 2017.
Procter & Gamble Co is a consumer goods company.
The firm markets its products internationally through various channels which include mass merchandisers, grocery stores, membership club stores, drug stores, and department stores.
Procter & Gamble Co has a market cap of $233.47 billion; its shares were traded at around $91.44 with a P/E ratio of 16.35 and P/S ratio of 3.85.
The dividend yield of Procter & Gamble Co stocks is 2.97%.
Procter & Gamble Co had annual average EBITDA growth of 0.50% over the past five years.
For the last quarter Procter & Gamble Co reported a revenue of $16.1 billion, compared with the revenue of $16.1 billion during the same period a year ago.
For the latest fiscal year the company reported a revenue of $65.1 billion, a decrease of 0.4% from the previous year.
For the last five years Procter & Gamble Co had an average revenue decline of 5.1% a year.
The reported diluted earnings per share was $5.59 for the year, an increase of 51.5% from previous year.
Over the last five years Procter & Gamble Co had an EPS growth rate of 4.3% a year.
The Procter & Gamble Co enjoyed an operating margin of 21.45%, compared with the operating margin of 20.58% a year before.
The 10-year historical median operating margin of Procter & Gamble Co is 19.58%.
The profitability rank of the company is 6 (out of 10).
At the end of the fiscal year, Procter & Gamble Co has the cash and cash equivalents of $5.6 billion, compared with $7.1 billion in the previous year.
The long term debt was $18 billion, compared with $18.9 billion in the previous year.
The interest coverage to the debt is at a comfortable level of 30.
Procter & Gamble Co has a financial strength rank of 6 (out of 10).
At the current stock price of $91.44, Procter & Gamble Co is traded at 36.6% premium to its historical median P/S valuation band of $66.95 .
The P/S ratio of the stock is 3.85, while the historical median P/S ratio is 2.82.
The stock gained 8.53% during the past 12 months.
